rootItem.title: Version-agnostic anchor resource for codelist C170449

definition: Terminology relevant to the origin type for datasets in the Define-XML document.
name: Origin Type

terms.definition: A value that is derived through designation, such as values from a look up table or a label on a CRF.
A value that is actually observed and recorded by a person or obtained by an instrument.
A value that is calculated by an algorithm or reproducible rule, and which is dependent upon other data values.
A value that is not discoverable or accessible.
A value that is copied from a variable in another dataset.
A value that is included as part of the study protocol.
